    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/701: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 7, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. Department’s circular telegram December 7th, 4 p.m. I spoke with the
                    President of the Republic,<note n="47" xml:id="d90fn1">Manuel de Jesús Troncoso
                        de la Concha.</note> who had of course heard the news by radio. He asked me
                    to assure you that the Dominican Republic is our ally both in word and deed and
                    that we may count on its complete cooperation. He added that his Government will
                    take any and all measures that we desire.</p>
                <p>He added that the Dominican Congress has been convened for tonight at 9 p.m. to
                    take appropriate decisions on cooperation with us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
